 1999-08171999-05-040,  IA&ND,  ,  ,  , 
PrecisAppointments of PAUL LATOUR, of Yellowknife, Northwest Territories, as a member of the Renewable Resources Board, as nominated by the Department of the Environment; ROGER PEET, of Winnipeg, Manitoba, as a member of the Board, as nominated by the Department of Fisheries and Oceans; and MS. VICTORIA JOHNSTON, of Yellowknife, Northwest Territories, as an alternate member of the Board, as nominated by the Department of the Environment; reappointments of JOSEPH BENOIT, of Aklavik, Northwest Territories, as a member of the Board, as nominated by the Gwich'in Tribal Council; and JAMES B. FIRTH, of Inuvik, Northwest Territories, as a member of the Board, as nominated by the Council; appointments of ROBERT ALEXIE Sr., of Fort McPherson, Northwest Territories, as a member of the Board, as nominated by the Council; ROBERT ELIAS, of Fort McPherson, Northwest Territories, as an alternate member of the Board, as nominated by the Council; MS. MELBA MITCHELL of Aklavik, Northwest Territories, as an alternate member of the Board, as nominated by the Council; and NORM SNOWSHOE, of Inuvik, Northwest Territories, as an alternate member of the Board, as nominated by the Council, for a term of five years, unless removed from office for cause.
